{"title_page": "Morten Qvenild", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name        = Morten Qvenild\n| image       = Morten Qvenild.jpg\n| caption     = Morten Qvenild 2010\n| image_size  = 260px\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1978|08|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Kongsberg]], Norway\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| instrument  = Piano\n| background  = non_vocal_instrumentalist <!-- piano -->\n| genre       = [[Jazz]]\n| occupation  = Musician, composer\n| years_active  = \n| label           = [[Rune Grammofon]] <br/>[[ACT Music|ACT Records]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Susanna & the Magical Orchestra]], [[Solveig Slettahjell]], [[Jaga Jazzist]], [[Shining (Norwegian band)|Shining]]\n| website     = {{URL|vimeopro.com/nmh/sjangerfri-improvisasjon/video/90798346}}\n}}\n\n'''Morten Qvenild''' (born 31 August 1978 in [[Kongsberg]], Norway) is a Norwegian [[jazz]] pianist, band leader and producer.<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.grinningtroll.com/artist/Q/Qvenild_Morten.htm\n |title       = Morten Qvenild &ndash; Utgivelser\n |publisher   = grinningtroll.com\n |language    = Japanese\n |accessdate  = 2011-05-05\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20100105005854/http://www.grinningtroll.com/artist/Q/Qvenild_Morten.htm\n |archivedate = 2010-01-05\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.rockipedia.no/Vault.aspx?entity=62343\n| title = Morten Qvenild &ndash; Utgivelser\n| publisher = Rockipedia\n| accessdate = 2011-05-05\n}}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Morten Qvenild3.jpg|thumb|left|With In the Country, 2010]]\n[[File:Morten Qvenild - Kongsberg Kirke April 2011.jpg|thumb|260px|Solo concert, 2011]]\n[[File:MortenQuenild-Vossajazz2016.jpg|thumb|260px|Quenild and The HyPer (Sonal) Piano <br/>at [[Vossajazz]] 2016]]\nQvenild started his jazz career in the big band Ung Musikk in 1995, followed by studies on the Jazz program at the [[Norges Musikkh\u00f8gskole]]. He used to play in ''\u00d8stenfor Sol'' with [[Ole J\u00f8rn Myklebust]] among others, with Myklebust's OJ Trio, [[Shining (Norwegian band)|Shining]] (1999\u20132003) and [[Jaga Jazzist]] (2000\u20132002).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.groove.no/html/person/77412988.html |title=Morten Qvenild |publisher=Groove.no |accessdate=2014-04-15}}</ref>\n\nSince 2000 Qvenild is the \"orchestra\" of [[Magical Orchestra|Susanna & the Magical Orchestra]] and an original member of [[Solveig Slettahjell]]'s Slow Motion Quintet as well a duo partner. Beyond these enduring collaborations Qvenild is also involved in the [[Jon Klette]] Quartet, [[The National Bank (band)|The National Bank]] and he toured with [[Nils Petter Molv\u00e6r]]'s ''Khmer'' and with [[Bertine Zetlitz|Bertine Zetlitz Band]] (2003 and 2004).\n\nIn 2003 Morten Qvenild founded the trio In the Country with co-students [[Roger Arntzen]] (bass) and [[P\u00e5l Hausken]] (drums). They recorded five albums for [[Rune Grammofon]]. On the latter two \u2013''Whiteout'' (2009) and the live recorded ''Sounds and Sights'' (2011)\u2013 the band was joined by multi-instrumentalist [[Andreas Mj\u00f8s]]. Their last release was issued by the German ACT label.\n\nIn 2011 he performed with [[Marit Larsen]] a new version of [[Erik Bye]]'s ''V\u00e5r beste dag''. This has become [[NRK]]'s tune in their profile campaign.<ref>\n{{cite web\n| url=http://www.nrk.no/kultur-og-underholdning/1.7469280\n| title= Marit Larsen: &ndash; Glimrende initiativ\n| publisher = NRK.no\n| date = 2011-01-19\n| accessdate=2011-05-05\n}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 He took part, playing multiple instruments such as upright piano, harpsichord, harmonium, dulcitone, mandolinette, autoharp and kokles on [[a-ha]]'s MTV Unplugged recording of the Live Album, \"Summer Solstice\" in Giske, Norway and the Subsequent Unplugged tour in Jan and Feb 2018. He also Played keyboards for their \"Electric Summer\" Tour in June through August 2018.\n\n==Honors==\n*2004: \u00abJazzIntro\u00bb Award with the band ''In the Country'' at the [[Moldejazz]]<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.moldejazz.no/2010/index.php?page_id=12883\n| title = JazzIntro prisen\n| publisher = [[Moldejazz]]\n| accessdate = 2011-05-05\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304063048/http://www.moldejazz.no/2010/index.php?page_id=12883\n| archive-date = 2016-03-04\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref>\n*2004: [[Spellemannprisen]] in the class jazz with [[Solveig Slettahjell]] and pop music with [[The National Bank (band)|The National Bank]]<ref name=snl>{{cite web |url=http://snl.no/Morten_Qvenild |title=Morten Qvenild Biography |language=Norwegian |last=Hammer\u00f8 |first=Tor |publisher=[[Store Norske Leksikon]] |date=2009-02-14 |accessdate=2014-04-14}}</ref>\n*2007: [[Kongsberg Jazz Award]]<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.ballade.no/nmi.nsf/doc/art2007070715191787085374\n| title = Musikerprisen til Morten Qvenild\n| publisher = Norsk Musikkinformasjon\n| date = 2007-07-07\n| accessdate = 2011-05-05\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071123062208/http://www.ballade.no/nmi.nsf/doc/art2007070715191787085374\n| archive-date = 2007-11-23\n| url-status = dead\n}}</ref>\n*2016: [[Edvardprisen]] in the open class for the album ''Personal Piano''\n\n==Discography==\n{{main|Morten Qvenild Discography}}\n\n=== Solo albums ===\n*[[2015 in music|2015]]: ''Personal Piano'' ([[list of Hubro albums|Hubro Music]])\n*[[2016 in music|2016]]: ''The HyPer(Sonal) Piano Project - Towards A (Per)Sonal Topography Of Grand Piano And Electronics'' (Hubro Music)\n\n=== Collaborations ===\n;[[In the Country]]\n*[[2005 in music|2005]]: ''This Was the Pace of My Heartbeat'' ([[Rune Grammofon]])<ref name=snl/>\n*[[2006 in music|2006]]: ''Losing Stones, Collecting Bones'' (Rune Grammofon)\n*[[2009 in music|2009]]: ''Whiteout'' (Rune Grammofon)\n*[[2011 in music|2011]]: ''Sounds and Sights'' (Live album with DVD, Rune Grammofon)\n*[[2013 in music|2013]]: ''Sunset Sunrise'' (ACT)\n\n;[[Magical Orchestra|Susanna & the Magical Orchestra]] ([[Susanna Wallumr\u00f8d]])\n*[[2004 in music|2004]]: ''[[List of Lights and Buoys]]'' ([[Rune Grammofon]])\n*2006: ''Melody Mountain'' (Rune Grammofon)\n*2009: ''3'' (Rune Grammofon)<ref name=poesifestival>{{cite web |url=http://www.poesifestival.no/program/item/116-susanna-wallumr%C3%B8d.html |title=Susanna og det magiske |language=Norwegian |publisher=Norsk Musikkinformasjon Ballade.no |accessdate=2014-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{commons category|Morten Qvenild}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Portal|Norway|Jazz|Music}}\n*[http://www.groove.no/artist/77412988 Morten Qvenild Biography - Groove.no]\n*[http://www.mic.no/nmi.nsf/micdoc/art2008021811143533467154 Morten Qvenild Biography - Norsk musikkinformasjon MIC.no]\n*{{Discogs artist|Morten Qvenild}}\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=guvVk4BpqPE Morten Qvenild solo, live at Kongsberg church, 2011]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100601002715/http://nowhere.no/konsertfoto/tag/morten-qvenild/ Live Konsertfoto av Morten Qvenild]<sup>Where?</sup>\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{s-bef | before = [[H\u00e5vard Wiik]]}}\n{{s-ttl | title = Recipient of the [[Kongsberg Jazz Award]] | years = 2007}}\n{{s-aft | after = [[Helge Lien]]}}}\n{{s-bef | before = [[Tuva Syvertsen]] and [[Erik Sollid]] ([[Valkyrien Allstars]])}}\n{{s-ttl | title = Recipient of the open class [[Edvardprisen]] | years = 2016}}\n{{s-aft | after = [[Susanna Wallumr\u00f8d]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Shining (Norwegian band)}}\n{{Jaga Jazzist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qvenild, Morten}}\n[[Category:Jaga Jazzist members]]\n[[Category:20th-century Norwegian pianists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Norwegian pianists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian jazz pianists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian jazz composers]]\n[[Category:Avant-garde jazz musicians]]\n[[Category:Spellemannprisen winners]]\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kongsberg]]\n[[Category:Shining (Norwegian band) members]]\n[[Category:The National Bank (band) members]]\n[[Category:In the Country members]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name        = Morten Qvenild\n| image       = Morten Qvenild.jpg\n| caption     = Morten Qvenild 2010\n| image_size  = 260px\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1978|08|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Kongsberg]], Norway\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| instrument  = Piano\n| background  = non_vocal_instrumentalist <!-- piano -->\n| genre       = [[Jazz]]\n| occupation  = Musician, composer\n| years_active  = \n| label           = [[Rune Grammofon]] <br/>[[ACT Music|ACT Records]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Susanna & the Magical Orchestra]], [[Solveig Slettahjell]], [[Jaga Jazzist]], [[Shining (Norwegian band)|Shining]]\n| website     = {{URL|vimeopro.com/nmh/sjangerfri-improvisasjon/video/90798346}}\n}}\n\n'''Morten Qvenild''' (born 31 August 1978 in [[Kongsberg]], Norway) is a Norwegian [[jazz]] pianist, band leader and producer.<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.grinningtroll.com/artist/Q/Qvenild_Morten.htm\n |title       = Morten Qvenild &ndash; Utgivelser\n |publisher   = grinningtroll.com\n |language    = Japanese\n |accessdate  = 2011-05-05\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20100105005854/http://www.grinningtroll.com/artist/Q/Qvenild_Morten.htm\n |archivedate = 2010-01-05\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.rockipedia.no/Vault.aspx?entity=62343\n| title = Morten Qvenild &ndash; Utgivelser\n| publisher = Rockipedia\n| accessdate = 2011-05-05\n}}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Morten Qvenild3.jpg|thumb|left|With In the Country, 2010.]]\n[[File:Morten Qvenild - Kongsberg Kirke April 2011.jpg|thumb|260px|Solo concert, 2011.]]\n[[File:MortenQuenild-Vossajazz2016.jpg|thumb|260px|Quenild and The HyPer (Sonal) Piano <br/>at [[Vossa